22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fmarket-today-nov-wpi-dec-mfg-svcs-pmi-flash-fiis-dhanlaxmi-ipo-listing-124121600072_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Zakir%20Hussain%2C%204-Time%20Grammy%20Winner%20Who%20Gave%20Tabla%20A%20New%20Identity%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHis%20fingers%20flew%2C%20fluttered%20and%20floated%20in%20quicksilver%20changes%20of%20raga%20and%20rhythm%2C%20drumming%20up%20music%20and%20magic.%20Zakir%20Hussain%20was%20the%20maestro%20of%20tabla%2C%20percussionist%2C%20composer%20and%20even%20actor%20%E2%80%93%20a%20legend%20who%20was%20India's%20very%20own%20and%20yet%20belonged%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHussain%20died%20from%20'idiopathic%20pulmonary%20fibrosis'%2C%20a%20lung%20disease%2C%20in%20a%20San%20Francisco%20hospital%20early%20Monday.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftabla-maestro-zakir-hussain-dies-at-73-report-7257284%5C%22%3EHe%20was%2073%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20artiste%2C%20a%20marquee%20name%20in%20India%20and%20abroad%2C%20leaves%20behind%20more%20than%2060%20years%20of%20music.%20He%20played%20on%20the%20stage%20alongside%20some%20of%20the%20greatest%20Indian%20and%20international%20musicians%20in%20a%20fusion%20of%20Indian%20classical%20and%20world%20music%2C%20giving%20the%20tabla%20a%20whole%20new%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20great%20percussionist%20created%20music%20across%20genres%20and%20styles%2C%20including%20in%20his%20repertoire%20jazz%20and%20concertos%2C%20naturally%20developing%20an%20%E2%80%9Call-inclusive%20musical%20creativity%E2%80%9D%20after%20learning%20and%20playing%20under%20the%20tutelage%20of%20his%20father%20and%20renowned%20tabla%20player%2C%20Alla%20Rakha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20mindset%20as%20I%20was%20growing%20up%20tuned%20itself%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20music%20is%20music%2C%20it's%20not%20Indian%20music%20or%20that%20music%2C%20so%20when%20I%20actually%20started%20working%20with%20musicians%20who%20were%20non-Indian%20it%20seemed%20like%20a%20natural%20handshake%2C%26quot%3B%20Hussain%20told%20PTI%20almost%20a%20year%20ago%20ahead%20of%20a%20performance%20in%20Goa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20son%20of%20Alla%20Rakha%2C%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20tabla%20players%20of%20all%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpics-zakir-hussain-peerless-tabla-players-life-in-pictures-7255895%5C%22%3EHussain%20was%20to%20the%20music%20born%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20started%20early.%20The%20child%20prodigy%20performed%20his%20first%20concert%20at%20the%20age%20of%20seven%20and%20began%20touring%20at%2012.%20After%20completing%20his%20education%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20where%20he%20was%20born%2C%20he%20moved%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%201970.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20borders%20melted%20away%20when%20it%20came%20to%20his%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20Hussain%20became%20the%20first%20musician%20from%20India%20to%20receive%20three%20Grammys%20at%20the%2066th%20Annual%20Grammy%20Awards%20in%20February%20for%20Best%20Global%20Music%20Album%2C%20Best%20Global%20Music%20Performance%20and%20Best%20Contemporary%20Instrumental%20Album.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20overwhelmed%20and%20humbled%20by%20the%20outpouring%20of%20love%2C%20affection%2C%20and%20blessings%20for%20my%20multiple%20Grammy%20wins.%20It%20is%20impossible%20for%20me%20to%20individually%20respond%20to%20all%20of%20you%20but%20be%20assured%20that%20you%20are%20all%20in%20my%20heart%20and%20I'm%20bowing%20to%20each%20and%20every%20one%20of%20you%20in%20thanks.%20It%20was%20a%20great%20day%20for%20India%20at%20the%20Grammys%20and%20I'm%20proud%20to%20be%20carrying%20the%20national%20flag%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20Instagram%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%202024%20Grammys%2C%20Hussain%20earned%20his%20first%20honour%20for%20best%20global%20music%20album%20for%20%E2%80%9CThis%20Moment%E2%80%9D%20as%20part%20of%20the%20fusion%20music%20group%20Shakti%2C%20which%20includes%20founding%20member%20British%20guitarist%20John%20McLaughlin%2C%20as%20well%20as%20vocalist%20Shankar%20Mahadevan%2C%20violinist%20Ganesh%20Rajagopalan%20and%20percussionist%20Selvaganesh%20Vinayakram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20later%20won%20two%20other%20awards%20for%20the%20best%20global%20music%20performance%20for%20%26quot%3BPashto%26quot%3B%20and%20best%20contemporary%20instrumental%20album%20for%20%26quot%3BAs%20We%20Speak%26quot%3B%2C%20along%20with%20flautist%20Rakesh%20Chaurasia%2C%20American%20banjo%20player%20Bela%20Fleck%20and%20American%20bassist%20Edgar%20Meyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Shakti%20quintet%20reunited%20for%20a%20world%20tour%20in%20India%20to%20much%20excitement%20from%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20Shakti%2C%20Hussain%20also%20contributed%20to%20many%20groundbreaking%20collaborations%2C%20including%20Masters%20of%20Percussion%2C%20Planet%20Drum%20and%20Global%20Drum%20Project%20with%20Mickey%20Hart%2C%20Tabla%20Beat%20Science%2C%20Sangam%20with%20Charles%20Lloyd%20and%20Eric%20Harland%2C%20CrossCurrents%20with%20Dave%20Holland%20and%20Chris%20Potter%2C%20in%20trio%20with%20B%C3%A9la%20Fleck%20and%20Edgar%20Meyer%2C%20and%2C%20most%20recently%2C%20with%20Herbie%20Hancock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHussain%20composed%20three%20concertos.%20His%20third%2C%20the%20first-ever%20concerto%20for%20tabla%20and%20orchestra%2C%20was%20premiered%20in%20India%20in%20September%202015%2C%20by%20the%20Symphony%20Orchestra%20of%20India%2C%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20UK%20in%202016%2C%20and%20in%20the%20US%20in%20April%2C%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20composer%20who%20travelled%20and%20performed%20all%20across%20the%20globe%20had%20reservations%20against%20performing%20at%20private%20gatherings%20and%20disliked%20latecomers.%20He%20was%20also%20very%20vocal%20in%20his%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20conversation%20with%20author%20Nasreen%20Munni%20Kabir%20as%20written%20in%20her%20book%20%E2%80%9CZakir%20Hussain%3A%20A%20Life%20in%20Music%E2%80%9D%2C%20Hussain%20said%20a%20private%20gathering%2C%20corporate%20events%20or%20weddings%20are%20not%20places%20%E2%80%9Cwhere%20music%20should%20be%20heard%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThose%20are%20places%20where%20people%20come%20to%20socialize%2C%20to%20drink%20and%20perhaps%20have%20a%20meal.%20That's%20not%20the%20way%20music%20should%20be%20heard.%20For%20me%2C%20it's%20the%20concert%20hall%20or%20the%20theatre-people%20take%20their%20seats%2C%20the%20hall%20darkens%20and%20we%20musicians%20take%20our%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHussain%20would%20ask%20the%20organisers%20to%20close%20the%20doors%20once%20the%20performance%20begins%20and%20not%20allow%20latecomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20was%20the%20man%20himself.%20His%20broad%20smile%2C%20boyish%20good%20looks%20and%20curly%20locks%20keeping%20rhythm%20with%20his%20fingers%20gave%20him%20a%20distinctive%20star%20persona%20that%20sometimes%20went%20beyond%20his%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20percussionist%20was%20once%20voted%20the%20%E2%80%9Csexiest%20man%E2%80%9D%20by%20women%20readers%20of%20the%20Indian%20magazine%20%E2%80%9CGentleman%E2%80%9D%20in%201994%20in%20a%20competition%20against%20the%20likes%20of%20Amitabh%20Bachchan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20magazine%20team%20came%20to%20see%20me%20and%20wanted%20me%20to%20wear%20all%20these%20suits%20and%20jackets%20and%20Western%20clothes%20and%20feature%20on%20their%20cover.%20I%20think%20they%20were%20equally%20shocked%20and%20surprised%20that%20I%20won%20the%20greatest%20number%20of%20votes%20because%20they%20had%20assumed%20the%20winner%20would%20be%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hussain%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20Kabir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20his%20work%20as%20a%20tabla%20player%2C%20Hussain%20also%20composed%20music%20for%20many%20movies%2C%20including%20%26quot%3BManto%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BMr%20and%20Mrs%20Iyer%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20acted%20in%20the%20Merchant%20Ivory%20film%20production%20%26quot%3BHeat%20and%20Dust%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Perfect%20Murder%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BSaaz%26quot%3B%2C%20opposite%20Shabana%20Azmi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201988%2C%20Hussain%20became%20a%20household%20name%20as%20the%20face%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal%20Tea%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2033-second%20TV%20commercial%2C%20the%20ustad%20was%20shown%20immersed%20in%20his%20tabla%20riyaaz%2C%20only%20to%20later%20sip%20on%20a%20cup%20of%20Taj%20tea.%20The%20voiceover%2C%20by%20the%20famous%20Harish%20Bhimani%2C%20would%20then%20compliment%20Hussain's%20skills%20saying%20%26quot%3BWah%20Ustad%2C%20wah!%26quot%3B.%20To%20which%2C%20the%20percussionist%20would%20reply%3A%20%26quot%3BArre%20huzoor%2C%20wah%20Taj%20boliye!%26quot%3B%20That%20%E2%80%9CWah%20Taj%E2%80%9D%20became%20an%20oft%20used%20buzzword%20for%20many%20an%20occasion%2C%20and%20still%20remembered%20all%20these%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20year%2C%20Hussain%20also%20shared%20screen%20space%20with%20his%20father%20Allah%20Rakha%20in%20the%20iconic%20national%20integration%20song%20%26quot%3BMile%20Sur%20Mera%20Tumhara%26quot%3B%20which%20premiered%20on%20Doordarshan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20survived%20by%20his%20wife%20Antonia%20Minnecola%20and%20two%20daughters%2C%20Anisa%20Qureshi%20and%20Isabella%20Qureshi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20four%20Grammys%2C%20Hussain%20was%20the%20recipient%20of%20countless%20awards%20and%20honours%2C%20including%20Padma%20Shri%2C%20Padma%20Bhushan%2C%20Padma%20Vibhushan%2C%20Sangeet%20Natak%20Akademi%20Award%2C%20the%20USA's%20National%20Heritage%20Fellowship%20and%20Officier%20in%20France's%20Order%20of%20Arts%20and%20Letters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20his%20countless%20fans%20bid%20farewell%20to%20the%20arti