20and%20looked%20at%20all%20the%20houses%20on%20their%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20main%20bedroom.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6757f41e91c1cc343d479306%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221816%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20idea%20was%20to%20restore%20the%20akiya%20to%20its%20former%20glory%20but%20with%20some%20modern%20amenities.%3Cp%3ENekoAshi%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20Mitocho%2C%20a%20small%20town%20near%20Masuda%20city%2C%20where%20they%20found%20the%20perfect%20akiya%20%E2%80%94%20a%20traditional%20Japanese%20house%20constructed%20in%201868%2C%20during%20the%20Meiji%20era.%20Masuda%20city%20is%20about%20a%20two-hour%20drive%20from%20Hiroshima%2C%20and%20a%2090-minute%20flight%20from%20Tokyo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20drove%20over%20there%2C%20and%20when%20we%20saw%20it%2C%20we%20just%20knew%20that%20was%20the%20one%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20look%20anymore%20after%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Deborah%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20property%20had%20been%20vacant%20for%2012%20years%20before%20they%20came%20along.%20The%20couple%20was%20told%20it%20had%20served%20as%20a%20sake%20brewery%20until%20the%20early%201900s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20inspect%20the%20property%2C%20they%20had%20to%20fill%20out%20a%20couple%20of%20forms%20for%20the%20local%20akiya%20bank.%20An%20akiya%20bank%20is%20a%20database%20maintained%20by%20the%20local%20municipalities%20for%20abandoned%20or%20vacant%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sake%20brewery%20sign%20that%20the%20couple%20found%20in%20the%20akiya.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6757f62152dd0818d1a62557%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221816%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20akiya%20had%20been%20a%20sake%20brewery%20at%20some%20point%20in%20the%20past%2C%20and%20the%20couple%20found%